# CSS

**Agent:** Master theme owns tokens; feature CSS uses variables only — modern glass surfaces, soft gradients, layered depth, and shared motion. No hardcoded colors, fonts, or radii in feature files.

## File ownership

| Location | Owns |
|----------|------|
| Master CSS (`src/index.css` / theme entry) | Tokens, reset, scrollbars, `color-scheme`, global typography |
| Feature CSS (colocated) | BEM layout and component modifiers — **tokens only** |
| TSX inline `style` | Dynamic values only (bar width, position) — camelCase keys |

Scrollbar theming → master CSS only. No cross-feature class references.

## Never do

- Hardcoded hex/rgb/hsl/rgba in feature CSS when a token exists — **including every `linear-gradient` stop**
- Retheme one component while leaving stale literals in sibling feature CSS
- Instant state jumps — always transition interactive properties
- Heavy borders without matching shadow (feels flat)
- Theme fonts outside token stacks

See `react.mdc` (colocated CSS).
